Citation.sTitle: Liquid-Liquid Equilibria for Systems Composed by 1-Methyl-3-octylimidazolium Tetrafluoroborate Ionic Liquid, Thiophene, and n-Hexane or Cyclohexane
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid-liquid equilibrium data have been determined experimentally for {1-methyl-3-octylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate + thiophene + hexane} and {1-methyl-3-octylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate + thiophene + cyclohexane} ternary systems at 298.15 K. The compositions of the ends of the tie-lines were obtained by gas chromatographic analysis of phases at equilibrium. Data have been adequately correlated using the nonrandom two-liquid (NRTL) activity coefficient model despite this being an equation intended for nonelectrolyte solutions.
